{"id": "1407707667937493003", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "type": 19, "author_id": "272394963642220545", "author_name": "__goz__", "author_bot": false, "content": "> FOR TRANSLATORS AND PROOFREADERS:\n> 1. Fork the Project\n> 2. Create your Feature Branch\n> 3. Commit your Changes\n> 4. Push to the Branch\n> 5. Open a Pull Request\n> If you use Github Desktop check [this](https://docs.github.com/en/desktop/adding-and-cloning-repositories/cloning-and-forking-repositories-from-github-desktop) out.\nI believe all changes should be made on your local copie(s) and then sent for approval via github in the current workflow.\n\n-# quoting the README at https://github.com/BIAVGit/Morimens-Localizations/blob/main/README.md", "timestamp": "2025-08-20T12:47:41.980000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-08-20T12:49:27.970000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "🫡", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [{"type": "link", "title": "Cloning and forking repositories from GitHub Desktop - GitHub Docs", "url": "https://docs.github.com/en/desktop/adding-and-cloning-repositories/cloning-and-forking-repositories-from-github-desktop", "description": "You can use GitHub Desktop to clone and fork repositories that exist on GitHub."}, {"type": "article", "title": "Morimens-Localizations/README.md at main · BIAVGit/Morimens-Locali...", "url": "https://github.com/BIAVGit/Morimens-Localizations/blob/main/README.md", "description": "Contribute to BIAVGit/Morimens-Localizations development by creating an account on GitHub."}], "reply_to": "1407706718552592476", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
